title: [Beach Area, Rocky Shore]
description: A forest of poles, warped and bent by wind and weather, stand in mute rows.  This was where a long vanished fisherfolk spread their nets to dry.  North from here stands an ancient dock, now broken and twisted.

A forest of poles, warped and bent by wind and sun, stand in mute rows.  This was where a long vanished fisherfolk spread their nets to dry in the sun.  North from here stands an ancient dock, now broken and twisted.
